# RoboLedger V5.2.15: Layout Width Standardization

Unifying the width of all header components (Header Card, Action Bar, Switcher Bar) to ensure a perfectly aligned "Island Stack" at 1060px.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> **Width Enforcement**: The Header Card currently appears narrower than the Action Bar. I will enforce `width: 100%; max-width: 1060px;` to ensure perfect vertical alignment with the transaction grid.

## Proposed Changes

### UI Logic (app.js)
- **renderTransactionsRestored**:
  - Update `header-card` inline style to include `width: 100%`.
  - Fix `margin: auto` to `margin: 0 auto` for stricter box-model behavior.

### Styling (system.css)
- Review `.header-card` and `.v5-action-bar` to ensure they share identical `max-width` tokens and margin behaviors.
- Ensure the parent container `.v5-main-header` doesn't apply any width-restricting flex properties.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. **Vertical Alignment Check**: Use a browser inspector or visual guide to ensure the left and right edges of the Header Card, Action Bar, and Switcher Bar are perfectly flush with each other.
2. **Standardization Check**: Confirm that resizing the window maintains the 1060px centered islanding for all elements in the stack.

